						               													<description>Even if this is blasphemy, I have no regrets, all for prosperity&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The tyrant has fallen ill and a power struggle is taking place. The people who have been suffering from oppression are looking forward to the arrival of the virtuoso, but as venerable merchants, we must see reality rather than dreams.&amp;#10;What we should think about now is how to get into the influential people of the new era.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players embrace the powers to become the owner of a venerable merchant and solidify their position. It is also good to give a gift that the person in power likes. It is also good to use dark means. If you increase the influence of those in power with support, you will get a big reward, but sometimes you may benefit another family.&amp;#10;In addition to the normal mode for 2 to 4 people who can enjoy deep bargaining, a mode for 1 person is also installed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     A card game for 1 to 4 players who aims to be the best merchant with the joy of those in power.&amp;#10;     Is it a sweet candy to prepare to outsmart the business enemies? Or is it a black envelope?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-Equipped with a solo play mode to prevent the Bazzi-Betti family's plot&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game consists of 7 rounds , during which you will play a single card from your hand to one of your available contacts alter the influence board sometimes activating unique effects and then score for the position of that contact. &amp;#10;at the end of the game (and after end game scoring) the player with the most victory points will be the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Serviam is a hand management game in which players need to make decisions based on who they have contact with , who other players have contact with , positions of those contacts and if they should gift or threat them.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
